# Chapter 5 · Lesson 3 — build-context excludes for the query image.
#
# SECURITY ANGLE: the most important job of a .dockerignore in this lesson is
# keeping secrets and local state OUT of the build context, so they can never be
# copied into a layer by a broad `COPY . .` or leak via the context.
#
# PLACEMENT NOTE: Docker reads the .dockerignore from the *build-context root*.
# The demo builds from the repo root, so to take effect this file's rules must
# live in a root .dockerignore. This copy documents the intended rules for the
# lesson; see DEMO.md for the placement caveat.

# --- Secrets — never let these enter the build context ---
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
secrets/

# --- Local data / runtime state — must not leak into the image ---
chroma_data/
*.log

# --- Version control / project metadata ---
.git
.gitignore

# --- Python caches & build artifacts ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# --- Local virtualenvs — never ship the host's venv into the image ---
.venv/
venv/

# --- Editor / OS noise ---
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
